Here's how you would compute the powers of $\mathbf{A}$ and then add them up using Maple:

```
with(linalg):
A := Matrix([[3, 7], [ -1, -2 ]] );
A27 := A^27;
A31 := A^31;
A40 := A^40;
res := A27 + A31 + A40;
```

When you run this code, `res` will contain the sum of $\mathbf{A}^{27}$, $\mathbf{A}^{31}$, and $\mathbf{A}^{40}$. Note: If your CAS does not have a built-in matrix exponentiation function like Maple does, you may need to use a loop to calculate each power separately.
